# Pipeline & Polars Conventions

The pipeline is: state-portal download → schema-driven ingest → per-state
validation → unified cross-state model → PostgreSQL load.

## Polars

- Prefer `LazyFrame` over eager `DataFrame`; defer `.collect()` to the end of a
  pipeline.
- Never `.collect()` mid-pipeline then re-wrap as a `LazyFrame`.
- Write fluent method chains — one operation per line, readable top to bottom.
  Avoid intermediate-variable sprawl.
- Compose pipeline stages with `.pipe()`; each stage is a pure transform.
- Use Polars expressions for transforms — no `iterrows()`-style row iteration.
- pandas is for legacy interop only; new transforms use Polars.

## Ingestion & unification

- File parsing goes through `GenericFileReader` with schemas built via
  `build_schema_for_states([...])` — header normalization and type conversion
  are automatic.
- Every column a state file produces must have a mapping in the unified field
  library. Unmapped columns are a bug, not a silent drop.
- New state implementations inherit `StateCategoryClass` /
  `StateFileValidation` from `app/abcs/`.

## Data integrity

- Log row counts at every pipeline stage — never drop rows silently.
- Validate records with Pydantic/SQLModel before load.
- Attach `file_origin` and `download_date` metadata to loaded records.
- Parameterize all file paths; never hardcode them.
